# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AI Wellness Buddy — Frontend environment variables
# Copy to .env.local and fill in real values.
# NEVER commit .env.local to source control.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# In local development, the Next.js proxy (next.config.js rewrites) forwards
# all /api/* requests from http://localhost:3000 to the backend at
# http://localhost:8000.  No NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL is required — all API calls
# use the same origin, which eliminates CORS issues and ensures HttpOnly auth
# cookies are forwarded correctly.
#
# For Vercel / production deployments you will need to set up a rewrite or
# reverse-proxy in your hosting provider to forward /api/* to your backend.
# Example (Vercel vercel.json):
#   {
#     "rewrites": [{ "source": "/api/:path*", "destination": "https://api.your-domain.com/api/:path*" }]
#   }
